Did you see my followup questions from your report on 9/28?

&gt; Haven&#39;t seen that particular SEVERE log event in years -- pre-1.0.
&gt; 
&gt; Are all 67K occurrences for the same server (www.mit.edu:8000), or many 
&gt; servers?
&gt; 
&gt; Have any URIs been added to the crawl in a way other than as starting 
&gt; seeds or outlink-discovery?
&gt; 
&gt; What do the last 10-20 lines of the crawl.log for URIs on the 
&gt; &quot;www.mit.edu:8000&quot; server show -- any atypical negative error codes? If 
&gt; the &#39;http://www.mit.edu:8001/robots.txt&#39; URI appears in the crawl.log, 
&gt; seeing its full line (esp. the hopsPath and via) would be helpful.
&gt; 
&gt; This symptom seems to suggest that the 
&gt; &#39;http://www.mit.edu:8001/robots.txt&#39; URI was already at 
&gt; CandidateURI.HIGHEST (0) scheduling-directive, which by design should 
&gt; not occur: most URIs are at NORMAL (3); some seeds/embeds/prerequisites 
&gt; can be MEDIUM (2); prerequisites of those can be HIGH (1); and 
&gt; prerequisites of those can be HIGHEST (0). There really shouldn&#39;t be any 
&gt; prerequisite-of-prerequisite (&#39;PP&#39;) synthetic hops-paths -- and even a 
&gt; 2-long path should be a very rare event.
&gt; 
&gt; Using the form- or http-auth login features (which also schedule 
&gt; &#39;prerequisite&#39; URIs) might make such hops-paths more likely; are those 
&gt; in use on this crawl?


